- [x] …started working remotely from anywhere on this planet full time! This is **HUGE**. I even gave up my apartment back in Germany and I am now full time vagabond ;)
- [x] …stayed connected with good friends, this will be always be super important to me whilst I am traveling.
- [x] …updated an project from hapijs v16 to v17, promisify all the things!
- [x] …already finished filing taxes for 2017.
- [x] …wrote _a bunch_ of api route tests during that upgrade, never deploy anything without tests.
- [x] …started a new project with node.js/CouchDB/VueJS/Docker: https://www.stehauf.io. Let's see where this goes (currently in closed beta).
- [x] …set up a production deployment that goes from git push to production in less than five minutes. always deliver!
- [x] …hiked up to Lions Head in Cape Town and watched a beautiful sunset.
- [x] …went to visit the Zeitz Museum of Contemporary Art Africa. African art seems to be highly influenced by the topics violence and suffering :(
- [x] …got my yellow fever shot for future travels.
- [x] …upgraded to an iPhone X from my old 6. much photos, such quality!
- [x] …bought all-wooden sunglasses from Bello in Cape Town, because the plastic ones keep on breaking
- [x] …visited the Automattic office in Cape Town a few times. Thanks for having me!
